<subSubSection id="5CD63B7A621BF066D4B16E67A87F0917" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="87992EEFD9B1DCF33E5FDB0DE141199C" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD3F7C425E7117F914F271B871BFA297" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">
This species was described from 
<normalizedToken id="DD3C1E4C07781F8EAA0FC728E6460DCC" originalValue="Bahía">Bahia</normalizedToken>
Tenacatita, west of the islets off Barra de Navidad, between 45.7 and 64 m depth. A second species from Western Mexico is 
<taxonomicName id="B5A5E70DB1D0BACBADEAB1827B1F4E76" authorityName="Fauchald" authorityYear="1972" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Idanthyrsus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idanthyrsus armatopsis" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="armatopsis">
<emphasis id="097DAE5E84347674EE6295BF8728F990" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">Idanthyrsus armatopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fauchald, 1972 
<bibRefCitation id="F98B0B5F5BEDA7916621DAD9ECD58663" author="Fauchald, K" journalOrPublisher="Allan Hancock Monographs Marine Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" pagination="1 - 575" refId="B5999559" refString="Fauchald, K, 1972. Benthic polychaetous annelids from deep waters off Western Mexico and adjacent areas in the Eastern Pacific Ocean. Allan Hancock Monographs Marine Biology 7: 1 - 575" title="Benthic polychaetous annelids from deep waters off Western Mexico and adjacent areas in the Eastern Pacific Ocean" volume="7" year="1972">Fauchald (1972)</bibRefCitation>
described from bathyal depths (1200 -1400 m) in the Gulf of California. 
<taxonomicName id="A692155DE8F0498731169EBFD4BD8BCF" authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Idanthyrsus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idanthyrsus mexicanus" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="BDA98C5E9CB0E9FA5E168ABBDC298E33" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">Idanthyrsus mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EC70887E76997290E9CF798B46BE6855" genus="I." lsidName="I. armatopsis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" rank="species" species="armatopsis">
<emphasis id="9B356B7064DDF8628E2A417C9BA53CE3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">I. armatopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the presence of nuchal hooks without hoods, but the inner paleae in 
<taxonomicName id="698B592BA44B2B8FD00A40B47F52A59C" genus="I." lsidName="I. mexicanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="226D1FD3345AFE683BA4FEAE058ADE53" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">I. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have pointed tips versus blunt tips in 
<taxonomicName id="2FB62766A96C203127CDB0D60AE7A709" genus="I." lsidName="I. armatopsis." pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" rank="species" species="armatopsis.">
<emphasis id="6C7AECF21488E0C250DC53A98F657F87" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">I. armatopsis.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Number of teeth of abdominal uncini was not described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB3F759CEAFB3CCCE557E1AFEF8B5B2" author="Kirtley, D. W." journalOrPublisher="Sabecon Press, Scientific Series Florida, Florida" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" refId="B5999853" refString="Kirtley, D. W., 1994. A review and taxonomic revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida; Polychaeta. Sabecon Press, Scientific Series Florida, Florida" title="A review and taxonomic revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida; Polychaeta" year="1994">Kirtley (1994)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName id="F6D78D62C93EC871A914D4ECC07EEFD0" genus="I." lsidName="I. mexicanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="CF30C2AB28CDD7EAFB4CFC66D1B517B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">I. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but specimens here reported from Chamela Bay have six teeth in side view versus 7-8 teeth in 
<taxonomicName id="D7BDF323531B50CF88FB4ECDABE40876" genus="I." lsidName="I. armatopsis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" rank="species" species="armatopsis">
<emphasis id="A40E8F81686DBF908D72BFDAC99AB3B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">I. armatopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The median organ in 
<taxonomicName id="D3C3168334EF3F0C387DCEE67F2D0BC3" genus="I." lsidName="I. mexicanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="C4B579FE923D07F77D7852D540FF362D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">I. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(not described in original description by 
<bibRefCitation id="1145F5527DDCD9871B74F65042B8ECBE" author="Kirtley, D. W." journalOrPublisher="Sabecon Press, Scientific Series Florida, Florida" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" refId="B5999853" refString="Kirtley, D. W., 1994. A review and taxonomic revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida; Polychaeta. Sabecon Press, Scientific Series Florida, Florida" title="A review and taxonomic revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida; Polychaeta" year="1994">Kirtley 1994</bibRefCitation>
) is short, extending only 1/4 above lateral opercular lobes, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="9AC8232048D959C23601F1DFA4A56119" genus="I." lsidName="I. armatopsis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572" rank="species" species="armatopsis">
<emphasis id="6F6FB7DF1E8BE8ECFB8EA4924702E2AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57572">I. armatopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this organ extends 1/2 above lateral opercular lobes.
</paragraph>
